cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new technique to improve the training of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) by gradually increasing the task difficulty of the discriminator. The paper also involves experiments on image generation tasks, which are commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed technique also involves the use of neural networks, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the study of competition between the generator and discriminator, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics).
